premise_source_doc_sentence: Amerigo Vespucci  (  -LSB- ameˈriːɡo vesˈputtʃi -RSB- ; March 9 , 1454February 22 , 1512  )  was an Italian explorer , financier , navigator and cartographer who first demonstrated that Brazil and the West Indies did not represent Asia 's eastern outskirts as initially conjectured from Columbus ' voyages , but instead constituted an entirely separate landmass hitherto unknown to Old Worlders .

The Spanish ship San Miguel fixed their location at 52 ° 37 'S , 47 ° 49 ` W. On 20 February 1794 , they were sighted again by a Spanish survey ship , the corvette Atrevida , which as part of the Alejandro Malaspina circumnavigation had been sent to confirm them .
